body: same issue, the same setup / code works on macos

I had the same issue. Turns out that there is a onnxruntime.dll in C:\Windows\System32 that gets loaded instead of the onnxruntime.dll I'm linking with. Copying the correct dll next to the executable fixes it.

> Turns out that there is a onnxruntime.dll in C:\Windows\System32 that gets loaded instead of the onnxruntime.dll I'm linking with. 

I think a similar thing is reported here: https://github.com/dotnet/interactive/issues/967

Seems like load preferences aren't preferring a local copy of onnxruntime.dll over the one built into Windows.  I would expect that to be handled by onnruntime automatically.
